7 434      My mind as generous, and my shape as true,
7 435      As honest madam's issue? Why brand they us
7 436      With base? with baseness? bastardy? base, base?
7 437      Who, in the lusty stealth of nature, take
7 438      More composition and fierce quality
7 439      Than doth, within a dull, stale, tired bed,
7 440      Go to th' creating a whole tribe of fops
7 441      Got 'tween asleep and wake? Well then,
7 442      Legitimate Edgar, I must have your land.
7 443      Our father's love is to the bastard Edmund
7 444      As to th' legitimate. Fine word- 'legitimate'!
7 445      Well, my legitimate, if this letter speed, 
7 446      And my invention thrive, Edmund the base
7 447      Shall top th' legitimate. I grow; I prosper.
