7 4251   Edg. Look up, my lord.
7 4252   Kent. Vex not his ghost. O, let him pass! He hates him
7 4253      That would upon the rack of this tough world
7 4254      Stretch him out longer.
7 4255   Edg. He is gone indeed.
7 4256   Kent. The wonder is, he hath endur'd so long.
7 4257      He but usurp'd his life.
7 4258   Alb. Bear them from hence. Our present business
7 4259      Is general woe. [To Kent and Edgar] Friends of my soul, you
7 4260         twain
7 4261      Rule in this realm, and the gor'd state sustain.
7 4262   Kent. I have a journey, sir, shortly to go.
7 4263      My master calls me; I must not say no.
7 4264   Alb. The weight of this sad time we must obey,
7 4265      Speak what we feel, not what we ought to say.
7 4266      The oldest have borne most; we that are young
7 4267      Shall never see so much, nor live so long.
7 4268                                        Exeunt with a dead march.
